claudeqt (0.0.1-0qt6~ppa1~noble1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Phase 1 scaffold: initial source package layout per
    docs/phase-1.md §5.2. Ships three binary packages — claudeqt
    (GUI), claudeqt-remote (headless daemon), claudeqt-common
    (arch:all shared data) — built against the KF5 syntax-highlighting
    Qt6 backport shipped in the same PPA (kf5syntaxhighlighting-qt6).
  * claudeqt is a QLabel stub at this phase; src/app/main.cpp only
    validates that the CMake graph + Qt6 + KF5-qt6 + cmark-gfm +
    libsqlite3 + Python3 link together cleanly and that the
    packaging path produces a runnable ELF.
  * claudeqt-remote is the signalfd+timerfd+sd_notify watchdog stub
    described in phase-1.md §8.3 — Type=notify, WatchdogSec=30,
    10 s WATCHDOG=1 cadence — so the §12 DoD fault-injection test
    has a real live daemon to poke from day one.
  * debian/rules uses dh-cmake with cmake+ninja buildsystem and
    -DCLAUDEQT_SYSTEM_INTEGRATION=ON -DBUILD_TESTING=OFF.
  * claudeqt-remote postinst creates the dedicated system user
    `claudeqt` (home /var/lib/claudeqt, shell /usr/sbin/nologin),
    generates a self-signed Ed25519 TLS cert under /etc/claudeqt/certs,
    and prints state-aware NEXT STEPS hints per phase-1.md §7.5.
  * claudeqt-remote unit defaults to IPAddressDeny=any +
    IPAddressAllow=localhost; admins extend via drop-in files in
    /etc/systemd/system/claudeqt-remote.service.d/ (additive merge
    of IPAddressAllow= across drop-ins).
  * Noble-only in Phase 1; Resolute upload will follow when the
    port is validated. Version suffix `-0qt6~ppa1~noble1` keeps the
    `qt6` marker (explicit signal that this is the Qt6 build path)
    and the `~ppa<N>~<distro>N` HobbyCAD convention.

 -- Aaron Yourk <ayourk@gmail.com>  Mon, 13 Apr 2026 22:00:00 -0400
